{"type":"message","id":"4956280a","parentId":"d8986ea1","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:50:25.582Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_34flagatmp03_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 104917\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful single action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI analysis done - found that 44.8% of invariants are noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This will compare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\nI should look at the CFI_RESULTS.md to understand the data structure, then design and implement the experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: implement a CFI-weighted compression script that:\r\n1. Loads the invariant frequency data\r\n2. Applies CFI weighting to prioritize high-CFI invariants\r\n3. Compares next-pulse prediction quality vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nThis advances the pending \"CFI-weighted compression experiment\" task.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis revealed only 5.7% of invariants are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). The pending experiment needs to quantify whether CFI-weighting improves next-pulse prediction over frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` documenting the experimental design to compare CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression for next-pulse prediction, using the existing invariant frequency data from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Objective\r\nCompare next-pulse prediction quality between:\r\n1. **Frequency baseline** - compress by invariant frequency only\r\n2. **CFI-weighted** - compress by CFI x frequency (prioritizes causal stability)\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will better predict which invariants persist into next session, because high-CFI invariants represent true causal anchors rather than metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n## Data Source\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` - 17,718 invariants with frequency and CFI scores\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Metric: Next-Pulse Persistence Rate\r\nFor each invariant in session N:\r\n- **Predicted persistence** = invariant included in compressed representation\r\n- **Actual persistence** = invariant appears in session N+1\r\n\r\n### Compression Ratios to Test\r\n- 99th percentile (keep top 1%)\r\n- 95th percentile (keep top 5%)\r\n- 90th percentile (keep top 10%)\r\n\r\n### Scoring Functions\r\n\r\n**Frequency-only:**\r\n```\r\nscore_freq(v) = frequency(v)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**CFI-weighted:**\r\n```\r\nscore_cfi(v) = CFI(v) x log(frequency(v) + 1)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n| Compression | Frequency Baseline | CFI-Weighted |\r\n|-------------|-------------------|--------------|\r\n| Top 1%     | ~X% persistence   | ~Y% persistence |\r\n| Top 5%     | ~X% persistence   | ~Y% persistence |\r\n| Top 10%    | ~X% persistence   | ~Y% persistence |\r\n\r\nIf hypothesis holds: CFI-weighted achieves same compression with higher persistence OR higher compression with same persistence.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nRun against pulse history to measure actual persistence rates.\r\n\r\n## Status: PENDING\r\nAwaiting script implementation.\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:49:39"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":948,"aggregated":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 104917\r\n\r\n## Applied Mutations\r\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\r\nRejected: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md (missing)\r\n\r\n## LLM Response\r\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine the most impactful single action.\r\n\r\nCurrent situation:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI analysis done - found that 44.8% of invariants are noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This will compare CFI-weighted compression vs frequency baseline for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\nI should look at the CFI_RESULTS.md to understand the data structure, then design and implement the experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete action: implement a CFI-weighted compression script that:\r\n1. Loads the invariant frequency data\r\n2. Applies CFI weighting to prioritize high-CFI invariants\r\n3. Compares next-pulse prediction quality vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nThis advances the pending \"CFI-weighted compression experiment\" task.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nCFI analysis revealed only 5.7% of invariants are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7). The pending experiment needs to quantify whether CFI-weighting improves next-pulse prediction over frequency-only baseline.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` documenting the experimental design to compare CFI-weighted vs frequency-only compression for next-pulse prediction, using the existing invariant frequency data from `research/CFI_RESULTS.md`.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n\r\n## Objective\r\nCompare next-pulse prediction quality between:\r\n1. **Frequency baseline** - compress by invariant frequency only\r\n2. **CFI-weighted** - compress by CFI x frequency (prioritizes causal stability)\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will better predict which invariants persist into next session, because high-CFI invariants represent true causal anchors rather than metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n## Data Source\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` - 17,718 invariants with frequency and CFI scores\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Metric: Next-Pulse Persistence Rate\r\nFor each invariant in session N:\r\n- **Predicted persistence** = invariant included in compressed representation\r\n- **Actual persistence** = invariant appears in session N+1\r\n\r\n### Compression Ratios to Test\r\n- 99th percentile (keep top 1%)\r\n- 95th percentile (keep top 5%)\r\n- 90th percentile (keep top 10%)\r\n\r\n### Scoring Functions\r\n\r\n**Frequency-only:**\r\n```\r\nscore_freq(v) = frequency(v)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**CFI-weighted:**\r\n```\r\nscore_cfi(v) = CFI(v) x log(frequency(v) + 1)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n| Compression | Frequency Baseline | CFI-Weighted |\r\n|-------------|-------------------|--------------|\r\n| Top 1%     | ~X% persistence   | ~Y% persistence |\r\n| Top 5%     | ~X% persistence   | ~Y% persistence |\r\n| Top 10%    | ~X% persistence   | ~Y% persistence |\r\n\r\nIf hypothesis holds: CFI-weighted achieves same compression with higher persistence OR higher compression with same persistence.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nRun against pulse history to measure actual persistence rates.\r\n\r\n## Status: PENDING\r\nAwaiting script implementation.\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\r\n\r\n## For Next Instantiation\r\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\r\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:49:39","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774363825579}}
