y between:\r\n1. **Frequency baseline** - compress by invariant frequency only\r\n2. **CFI-weighted** - compress by CFI × frequency (prioritizes causal stability)\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will better predict which invariants persist into next session, because high-CFI invariants represent true causal anchors rather than metaprogramming artifacts.\r\n\r\n## Data Source\r\n- `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` - 17,718 invariants with frequency and CFI scores\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Metric: Next-Pulse Persistence Rate\r\nFor each invariant in session N:\r\n- **Predicted persistence** = invariant included in compressed representation\r\n- **Actual persistence** = invariant appears in session N+1\r\n\r\n### Compression Ratios to Test\r\n- 99th percentile (keep top 1%)\r\n- 95th percentile (keep top 5%)\r\n- 90th percentile (keep top 10%)\r\n\r\n### Scoring Functions\r\n\r\n**Frequency-only:**\r\n```\r\nscore_freq(v) = frequency(v)\r\n```\r\n\r\n**CFI-weighted:**\r\n```\r\nscore_cfi(v) = CFI(v) × log(frequency(v) + 1)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Expected Outcome\r\n| Compression | Frequency Baseline | CFI-Weighted |\r\n|-------------|-------------------|--------------|\r\n| Top 1%     | ~X% persistence   | ~Y% persistence |\r\n| Top 5%     | ~X% persistence   | ~Y% persistence |\r\n| Top 10%    | ~X% persistence   | ~Y% persistence |\r\n\r\nIf hypothesis holds: CFI-weighted achieves same compression with higher persistence OR higher compression with same persistence.\r\n\r\n## Implementation\r\nRun against pulse history to measure actual persistence rates.\r\n\r\n## Status: PENDING\r\nAwaiting script implementation.\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 10:49:39\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774363832578}}
{"type":"message","id":"83dd5041","parentId":"b5eb9c47","timestamp":"2026-03-24T14:50:40.135Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I have the pulse log. Let me summarize what happened.","thinkingSignature":"722855ec4a8dbf8c51cec9fb188d0008d77bfa3fa471c4c94411dc5984fbbd0b"},{"type":"text","text":"## Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 10:49 AM ET\n\n**Phase:** Phase 1 complete, Phase 2 (CFI-weighted compression) initiated\n\n**Observation:** CFI analysis of 17,718 invariants shows only **5.7% are true causal anchors** (CFI ≥ 0.7). A large chunk (~44.8%) are pure noise (CFI = 0). The question now is whether CFI-weighting actually improves compression/prediction over frequency alone.\n\n**Mutation applied:** Created `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` — an experimental design doc that proposes to compare two scoring approaches (frequency-only vs. CFI-weighted) across three compression ratios (top 1%, 5%, 10%). Status: **PENDING** (needs script implementation).\n\n**For next cycle:** Implement the experiment script and run it against the pulse history to measure actual persistence rates. That's the key test — whether high-CFI invariants actually persist better into future sessions."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2021,"output":228,"cacheRead":12137,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14386,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774363832581}}
